article.headline: Florida 95, Longwood 69
article.story: GAINESVILLE, Fla. -- Nick Calathes scored 19 points, Erving Walker had 16 and Kenny Kadji added 14 as Florida routed Longwood 95-69 on Tuesday night. Florida (13-2) couldn?t shake the pesky Lancers early in the first half, but took control with 7:37 to play before halftime when Allan Chaney slammed an offensive rebound for a 28-26 lead. The Gators? Walter Hodge followed that with a 3-pointer 20 seconds later as Florida began to roll from there. The Gators shot 59.4 percent percent from the field (38 of 64) in winning their ninth straight game, and Calathes also contributed eight assists and grabbed 10 rebounds. Antwan Carter led the Lancers (7-9) with 13 points, while Billy Robinson Jr. had 12 and Dana Smith added 10. Florida opens its Southeastern Conference schedule against Mississippi on Jan. 10.
